gm skill rename + install (gm-method). The skill DIRECTORY is skills/gm (not skills/gm-skill); the directory name is the slash command, so the command is /gm and the personal install path is ~/.claude/skills/gm/. The npm PACKAGE id stays gm-skill (unchanged) -- rename the dir and command, never the package. Installer bin/install.js (exposed as `npx gm-skill install`) needs NO npx skills library: it copies the bundled skills/gm dir into ~/.claude/skills/gm and ~/.agents/skills/gm (or ./.claude/skills/gm with --project), removing any legacy gm-skill dir first. Two modes: interactive OFFERS the Claude Code settings, non-interactive (--yes or non-TTY) SETS them outright and prints an explainer. The four settings: autoCompactEnabled=true, autoCompactWindow=380000 (ABSOLUTE token count = 38% of 1M, NOT a percentage), effortLevel=low (thinking effort), alwaysThinkingEnabled=false (thinking off). Explainer frames it as reasoning-in-code: the model still reasons by running hypotheses as code/browser probes and reading real results, replacing hidden thinking tokens with witnessed execution. test.js checkRenameAndInstaller runs the real installer into a temp HOME as the witness.